                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.01 Foreign Control/168: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Greene</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-12-12T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 12, 1931—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>167. Your telegram No. 199, December 3, 3 p.m.<note n="55" xml:id="d738fn55">Not
                        printed.</note> Please transmit the following to the Secretary General:
                        <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“The American member of the Committee appointed to study the problem
                            raised by the Liberian Government’s request for assistance has received
                            the note of the Secretary General, dated December 1, 1931,<note n="55"
                                xml:id="d738fn56">Not printed.</note> informing the members of the
                            Committee that its next meeting has been fixed for the middle of
                            January.</p>
                        <p>In reply, the American Member has the honor to state that his Government
                            is prepared to participate in the session.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>You may add informally that Reber expects to sail on January 2 and to arrive in
                    Geneva about the 10th of the month.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
